Commentary Text: Boult to Pooran, out Lbw!! Pooran has been adjudged lbw, has a word with his partner and walks off. This was on the cards. Pooran struggled to put bat on ball and this time he perishes. Full and angled in, Pooran misses the flick to wear it on his front pad adjacent to the sticks. Boult went down on one knee for a vociferous appeal and umpire Ulhas Gandhe took little time to raise the dreaded finger. That would have probably gone onto hit leg. SRH in a spot of bother here chasing a big score! Pooran lbw b Boult 0(9)

Commentary Text: Prasidh to Williamson, out Caught by Padikkal!! Edged, dropped and taken! Williamson stays, the umpires join and send it upstairs. 136.5kph, back of a length ball around off, Williamson gets squared up as he pokes. The outside edge flies to the right of Samson who dives and goes for a one-handed catch. The ball pops up and Padikkal shows great reflexes at first slip to dive forward and snaffle with both hands inches above the ground. The third umpire has a look at couple of angles and rules it in favour of the fielding team. Williamson c Padikkal b Prasidh 2(7)
